# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# Virtual environments (the dev venv is local, never committed)
.venv/
venv/

# Build artifacts (PyInstaller output, produced on Windows at M8)
build/
dist/

# Vendored wheels are a LOCAL build input only (a ~94 MB win_amd64 set), re-fetched via
# `pip download -r requirements-win.txt`. NOT committed (binary bloat / GitHub's 100 MB/file limit);
# vendor/wheels-sources.md records the exact version + sha256 + source URL of each, and the M8
# installer bundles them so the target needs no Python/network. The record + generator under
# vendor/ ARE committed — only the .whl payloads are ignored.
vendor/wheels/
# throwaway pip --report used to regenerate vendor/wheels-sources.md
/report.json

# Secrets & credentials — belt-and-braces (G7). Nothing here is committed today; these patterns exist
# so that a stray file never becomes a public-repo leak that only a history rewrite can undo.
# *.pfx is the live one: Authenticode code signing is a carried follow-up (PROGRESS.md), and a signing
# cert lands in the tree as exactly this.
*.pfx
*.pem
*.key
.env
*.log

# OS cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Claude Design export bundle, downloaded locally as reference. Its assets are imported into
# ui/icons/ + assets/brand/, so this duplicate (plus its .dc.html/support.js preview scaffolding)
# is deliberately NOT committed.
/design_handoff_sheaf_brand/
